history.content: You can't.  You used the swap function (most likely) during phase 1 because it allowed you to effectively waitlist for over your unit cap. You jumped ahead of the line effectively for CS162 over students who waited until phase 2; that's not a problem because that's what the swap function is set up to allow you to do. You can't now protect yourself from the risk of losing the other class (the negative part of the deal you made with the swap) and still keep the benefits (your place on the CS162 waitlist). It wouldn't be fair to other students.

I requested a swap for cs 162 at phase 1, but since the waitlist is so long, the swap request is still alive. Is it possible to cancel the swap request, without losing my waitlist position of CS 162, nor dropping the class I used to swap?
history.subject: How to cancel swap request without dropping classes?
